  "text": "To assess the lipid peroxidation, TBARS assay was performed according to the protocol published elsewhere (Okhawa et al., 1979; [CITATION_1] . The homogenate was centrifuged at 4,000 x g for 10 min to yield a pellet that was discarded and the supernatant was used for determining MDA content. 100 µL low speed supernatant was incubated for 60 min at 37°C in the presence or absence of extract. After incubation, TBA, 8.1% SDS and acetate buffer was added and again incubated for 60 min at 100°C. The production of light pink color showed the reaction of MDA with TBA. By cooling the tubes using ice, absorbance was measured at 532 nm using spectrophotometer.",
